createfirewalls.py / filters.py is a script to take firewall data from puppet
(or another host configuration framework), and convert them into Juniper/SLAX
configs.

Trivial example input files are in testdata/
Run the set with:

./createfirewall.py test.slax testdata/ && cat test.slax

Or, in a more normal, usage, format:

createfirewall.py [<output file> [<source directory>]]

